    "caption": "I turn the gritty pages, the scent of vanilla and aged ink:\n\nAngelic wonder, a soft bloom of untainted grace.\n\nGlacial eyes, the heavy stillness before the storm.\n\nSun-tipped brim, wearing the day with nonchalant ease.\n\nA smile on fire, burning with the weight of her own ambition.\n\nSharp angles, the calculated precision of a measured mind.\n\nYoung features weathering the first true weight of the man.\nDrifting through the rhythm of the rails, eyes wide and searching for a focus that won't hold.\n\nSlick with midnight gloss, a stilled enchantment.\n\nSavoring the iron tang of a heart torn open by the violet bruise of a bitten lip, blooming in the heavy silence—a map of everything we haven't said and a future we haven't dared to name.",
